---
// Static page — no data fetching needed
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width" />
    <title>About — Pokédex</title>
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Nunito:wght@400;600;700;800&display=swap" rel="stylesheet" />
    <style>
      * { margin: 0; padding: 0; box-sizing: border-box; }
      body { font-family: 'Nunito', sans-serif; background: #ffffff; color: #1a1a1a; min-height: 100vh; }
      nav { display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; padding: 1.5rem 2rem; border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(0,0,0,0.08); }
      nav a { color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: none; margin-left: 2rem; opacity: 0.6; font-weight: 600; }
      nav a:hover { opacity: 1; }
      .logo { font-weight: 800; font-size: 1.25rem; color: #f97316; }
      main { max-width: 800px; margin: 4rem auto; padding: 0 2rem; }
      h1 { font-size: 2.5rem; font-weight: 800; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
      h1 span { color: #f97316; }
      .lead { font-size: 1.15rem; opacity: 0.5; margin-bottom: 3rem; line-height: 1.7; }
      .grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(220px, 1fr)); gap: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 3rem; }
      .card { background: #fff7ed; border: 1px solid rgba(0,0,0,0.06); border-radius: 16px; padding: 1.5rem; }
      .card h2 { font-size: 1rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; color: #f97316; font-weight: 800; }
      .card p { font-size: 0.9rem; opacity: 0.6; line-height: 1.6; }
      .cta { text-align: center; margin-top: 2rem; }
      .btn { background: #f97316; color: white; padding: 0.875rem 2rem; border-radius: 8px; text-decoration: none; font-weight: 700; }
      .btn:hover { background: #ea6c00; }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <nav>
      <span class="logo">Pokédex</span>
      <div>
        <a href="/">Home</a>
        <a href="/pokedex">Pokédex</a>
        <a href="/about">About</a>
      </div>
    </nav>
    <main>
      <h1>The <span>Pokémon</span> World</h1>
      <p class="lead">Pokémon are creatures of all shapes and sizes who live in the wild or alongside humans. There are currently over 1000 known species, each with unique abilities, types, and stats.</p>
      <div class="grid">
        <div class="card">
          <h2>18 Types</h2>
          <p>Every Pokémon has one or two types — Fire, Water, Grass, Electric, and 14 more. Types determine strengths and weaknesses in battle.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h2>9 Generations</h2>
          <p>New Pokémon are introduced with each game generation, starting with 151 original species in Generation I (1996) up to 1025+ today.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h2>6 Base Stats</h2>
          <p>Each Pokémon has HP, Attack, Defense, Special Attack, Special Defense, and Speed. These determine performance in battles.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h2>PokéAPI</h2>
          <p>This Pokédex is powered by PokéAPI — a free, open RESTful API serving over 2.5 billion calls per month with data on every Pokémon.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="cta">
        <a href="/pokedex" class="btn">Explore the Pokédex</a>
      </div>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>